Customer Purchase Behavior Analysis

Project Overview

This project analyzes customer purchase behavior using a dataset containing transaction details, product categories, and spending patterns. The goal is to identify trends, optimize marketing strategies, and provide data-driven insights into customer shopping habits.

Dataset

File: shopping_trends.csv

Source: Customer purchase records from various store locations.

Columns: Customer ID, Transaction Date, Product Category, Purchase Amount, Payment Method, Store Location, Customer Segment.

Analysis Conducted

Data Cleaning & Preparation

Handled missing values and duplicates.

Standardized date formats and numerical fields.

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Visualized purchase trends over time.

Identified top-selling product categories.

Analyzed payment method preferences.

Evaluated regional sales performance.

Customer Segmentation

Grouped customers based on spending habits.

Identified high-value customers.

Predictive Insights

Used statistical analysis to detect seasonal trends.

Suggested marketing strategies based on findings.

